🔵 What is Shield in 2 Lines
AWS Shield is a managed DDoS protection service that protects your AWS applications from Distributed Denial of Service attacks.

The most dangerous modern DDoS attacks happen at Layer 7 because they look like normal HTTP traffic, which is why Shield Advanced + WAF together is the production-grade combo.

Think of it as a army protecting your building — WAF is the security guard at door, Shield is the army outside ✅

WAF                          Shield
────────────────             ────────────────
Layer 7 protection           Layer 3, 4, 7
HTTP attacks                 DDoS attacks
SQL injection, XSS           Flood attacks
Application level            Network level
Manual rules                 Automatic ✅

